### Blog API — Test Suite
### Requires Firebase Emulators running (npm run serve)
### Base URL: http://127.0.0.1:5001/ssrtest-cebd9/us-central1

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────
### Variables
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────
@baseUrl = http://127.0.0.1:5001/ssrtest-cebd9/us-central1
@authToken = owner
### NOTE: "owner" is a Firebase Auth emulator bypass token.
### It works ONLY in the emulator. For production, use a real Firebase ID token.
@postId = REPLACE_WITH_ACTUAL_POST_ID

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────
### Phase 1: Core CRUD
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────

### 1. Create a blog post (authenticated)
POST {{baseUrl}}/createPost
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "title": "Getting Started with Firebase",
  "text": "Firebase is a powerful platform that provides backend services for web and mobile applications. In this post, we'll explore the basics of Cloud Functions and Realtime Database.",
  "category": "tech",
  "imgUrl": "https://example.com/images/firebase-intro.jpg"
}

### 1a. Create another blog post (tech)
POST {{baseUrl}}/createPost
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "title": "TypeScript Best Practices in 2026",
  "text": "TypeScript continues to evolve with new features. Here are the best practices every developer should follow this year.",
  "category": "tech",
  "imgUrl": "https://example.com/images/typescript.jpg"
}

### 1b. Create a blog post (design)
POST {{baseUrl}}/createPost
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "title": "UI Design Principles for Beginners",
  "text": "Understanding the fundamental principles of UI design can dramatically improve your applications. Learn about contrast, repetition, alignment, and proximity.",
  "category": "design",
  "imgUrl": "https://example.com/images/ui-design.jpg"
}

### 1c. Create a blog post (science)
POST {{baseUrl}}/createPost
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "title": "Quantum Computing Explained Simply",
  "text": "Quantum computing may sound complex, but the core concepts are accessible. This post breaks down qubits, superposition, and entanglement.",
  "category": "science",
  "imgUrl": "https://example.com/images/quantum.jpg"
}

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────

### 2. List all blog posts (no auth required)
GET {{baseUrl}}/getPosts

### 2a. List posts with pagination
GET {{baseUrl}}/getPosts?page=1&limit=2

### 2b. List posts filtered by category
GET {{baseUrl}}/getPosts?category=tech

### 2c. List posts filtered by title containing word
GET {{baseUrl}}/getPosts?title=Firebase

### 2d. List posts filtered by text containing word
GET {{baseUrl}}/getPosts?text=TypeScript

### 2e. List posts filtered by author
GET {{baseUrl}}/getPosts?author=owner

### 2f. List posts filtered by views greater than
GET {{baseUrl}}/getPosts?view=gt&val=0

### 2g. List posts filtered by views equal
GET {{baseUrl}}/getPosts?view=eq&val=0

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────

### 3. Get single blog post (authenticated)
### Requires {{postId}} to be replaced with an actual post ID from the create response
GET {{baseUrl}}/getPost
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "postId": "{{postId}}"
}

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────

### 4. Update a blog post (authenticated, owner only)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/updatePost
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "postId": "{{postId}}",
  "title": "Getting Started with Firebase — Updated",
  "text": "Updated content for this blog post."
}

### 4a. Update only imgUrl
PUT {{baseUrl}}/updatePost
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "postId": "{{postId}}",
  "imgUrl": "https://example.com/images/new-image.jpg"
}

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────

### 5. Delete a blog post (authenticated, owner only)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/deletePost
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "postId": "{{postId}}"
}

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────
### Auth Error Tests
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────

### 5a. Create post without auth (should return 401)
POST {{baseUrl}}/createPost
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Unauthorized Post",
  "text": "This should fail",
  "category": "tech"
}

### 5b. Create post with invalid auth (should return 401)
POST {{baseUrl}}/createPost
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer invalid_token

{
  "title": "Invalid Token Post",
  "text": "This should fail",
  "category": "tech"
}

### 5c. Create post without required fields (should return 400)
POST {{baseUrl}}/createPost
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "title": "Missing text field"
}

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────
### Phase 6: Reports
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────

### 6. Get all reports (authenticated)
GET {{baseUrl}}/getReports
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 6a. Get reports by date (authenticated)
GET {{baseUrl}}/getReports?date=15-08-2026
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
